    "causal_summary": "The 5-iteration improvement research found the deep-loop architecture is sound but the C-plus routing guarantee is aspirational (the drift-guard test exists but nothing runs it; the guard + `/doctor` are hardcoded to the canonical skill, so a 2nd parent skill's `advisorRouting` is inert + unguarded), the runtime is \"MCP-free in name but parasitic on `system-spec-kit`'s nodemodules\", loop-locking is inconsistent (prose-only / missing across modes), and a set of low-regret hardening gaps exist",
